editorialReviews: Editorial Reviews Review Praise for The Last Kids on Earth series:"Terrifyingly fun! Max Brallier's The Last Kids on Earth delivers big thrills and even bigger laughs."--Jeff Kinney, author of the #1 New York Times bestseller Diary of a Wimpy Kid* "A perfect example of what an illustrated novel can and should be."--Kirkus Reviews, starred review* "Snarky end-of-the-world fun."--Publishers Weekly, starred review* "A gross-out good time with surprisingly nuanced character development."--School Library Journal, starred review"This series is a must-have for middle grade collections."--School Library Journal"The likable cast, lots of adventure, and gooey, oozy monster slime galore keep the pages turning."--Booklist"An apocalyptic adventure with a whole lot of heart."--Kirkus Reviews About the Author Max Brallier is a New York Times, USA Today, and Wall Street Journal bestselling author. His books and series include The Last Kids on Earth, Eerie Elementary, Mister Shivers, Galactic Hot Dogs, and Can YOU Survive the Zombie Apocalypse? He is a writer and producer for Netflix’s Emmy-award-winning adaptation of The Last Kids on Earth. Max lives in Los Angeles with his wife and daughter. Visit him at MaxBrallier.com. Douglas Holgate has been a freelance comic book artist and illustrator based in Melbourne, Australia, for more than ten years. He's illustrated books for publishers including HarperCollins, Penguin Random House, Hachette, and Simon & Schuster, and comics for Image, Dynamite, Abrams, and Penguin Random House.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MEET THE LAST KIDS ON EARTH: Jack Sullivan Self-proclaimed “zombie-fighting, monster-slaying tornado of cool!” (His friends would disagree with the “cool” part.)Every post-apocalyptic action hero needs a weapon, and Jack's is the Louisville Slicer – a baseball bat turned monster-slaying bladeJack’s motto? “The apocalypse is better with buddies!”Hobbies include taking pics of new monsters, late night gaming sessions, and junk food barbeques MEET THE LAST KIDS ON EARTH: June Del Toro Expert at kicking zombie butt, slaying evil monsters, and having fun while doing itDiscovering that battling monsters—and throwing epic dance parties—is more fun with friendsForever wears a multi-purpose, monster-battling, blaster-gadget on her left handDo NOT call her a damsel in distress. Seriously… DO NOT. MEET THE LAST KIDS ON EARTH: Quint Baker Super-rad scientist kid who’s always ready to save the dayCreates monster-battling gadgets, zombie-defeating weapons, and his own comics!Obsessed with bad movies and good video gamesBuilt Big Mama, the team’s post-apocalyptic pick-up truck MEET THE LAST KIDS ON EARTH: Dirk Savage Former bully turned monster battling buddyThe most ferocious 7th grader to ever walk the halls of Parker Middle SchoolA true renaissance kid: loves gardening, old western movies, and (of course) taking out bad dudesSee those boxing wraps? Those are for punching things. Dirk's always punching things. Jack Sullivan June Del Toro Quint Baker Dirk Savage

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for grades 2-5
reviews.reviewText: My second grader loves these books. He is obsessed with diary of a Wimpy kid, so this was a great series to transition to! It’s good also for their vocabulary level and I didn’t find any words that were harder than “tactical“, or “contraption”. My son was also dying, laughing at some lines in the first book. I also appreciate the hardcover that will stand the test of time, and the rough hands of a seven-year-old.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Monster Box of Epic Adventures for Your Mini Explorer!
reviews.reviewText: Calling all monster-battling, treehouse-dwelling adventurers! Have I got the loot for you: The Last Kids on Earth: The Monster Box! This treasure chest of books, packed with the first three rip-roaring tales in Max Brallier's series, is guaranteed to blast your kiddo into a world of zompocalypse fun. ‍♀️Imagine: your little hero, sprawled on the floor, flashlight in hand, giggling as Jack Sullivan outsmarts gooey Blarg monsters and escapes drool-dripping Drool Globs. They'll race alongside Quint, the tech-wiz kid, and squeal with delight at the mischievous antics of rottweiler puppy Spike.But it's not all giggles and gizzards. This series tackles real themes of friendship, courage, and facing your fears, all woven into the action-packed plot. Your mini-hero will learn that even when the world goes bonkers, true friendship and a good dose of ingenuity can save the day.
